gomodel:SYNGO_3899  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Rodent postsynaptic density proteins identified with high confidence by LC-MS/MS (Table1).\n\n24/09/2018 Pim\n- The HnRNP-A3 like protein mentioned in Table 1 references accession CAA76339. In Uniprot this partial protein sequence shows 100% sequence indentity to the unreviewed HnRNP-A3 record Q5U3M2. The rest of the paper also investigates the HnRNP-A3 protein. I conclude that the protein references in Table 1 is also the HnRNP-A3 protein.. Experimental description: Rat and mouse PSD fractionation from whole brain.\n\n24/12/2018 Pim\n- The authors state that PSD's were prepared from \"Rats or mice\". I have selected 'rat' species for the annotated protein based on its rat accession number 'CAA76339'.\n- Overexpressed proteins are of unknown species. May be of human or rat species:\n\"cDNA was obtained from Kazusa Research Institute (21) (\"KIAA\" prefix) or cloned from a rat brain cDNA library constructed with Superscript 3 (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) ...\".\n- I have annotated to Mouse based on the proteomics data in Table 1." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" ;
        dc:date           "2018-09-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3899" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

